                    "company": "Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam (VU Amsterdam)",
                    "description": "In my research I focus on addressing the pernicious effects of societal polarisation within the public debate on refugee reception in the Netherlands, whilst aiming to find ways to enable what are deemed the democratically constructive effects of 'polarisation' (i.e.: creating space for the inclusion of profoundly different views not represented within hegemonic discourses). My research is affiliated to both the VU Institute for Societal Resilience\u2019s (ISR) Polarisation Lab and the Refugee Academy. For the latter, I am currently also engaged in a project called Learning Crossroads for Refugee Inclusion (see: https://refugeeacademy-learningcrossroads.nl) that examines the role of (Dutch) civil society initiatives in promoting refugees\u2019 inclusion.\n\nTeaching responsibilities:\n- Influencing Societal Participation (Course in Master's programme Sociology)\n- Research Lab: Interviewing and Coding/Analysis (Methodlogical Course in Master's programme Sociology)",
